Search Engine Information

Basic Usage

Enter the name or partial name of an item you wish to search for.

Example: trak will automatically apply wildcards to either end of the string, matching all items with "StatTrak" in their name.

Exact Phrases

You can wrap search terms in quotes if you want to match the entire phrase exactly.

Example: If you want specifically the original chroma case key, you can search for "Chroma Case Key" to avoid having results such as the Chroma 2 Case Key.

Excluding A Term

If you want to exclude a specific word or phrase from your search results, add a minus sign (-) to the beginning of the word. Make sure to avoid putting a space between this and the word you want to exclude!

Example: If you want all regular Bayonets but not M9 Bayonets, you can use Bayonet -M9
